parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Filler Neck Corrosion and Leaks
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion and leaks in the fuel filler neck can cause fuel to spill onto the ground, creating a fire hazard and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: corrosion in the fuel filler neck
gas splashing back from the filler neck onto the ground
small leaks after topping off or fill-ups
and gas pouring out for several minutes.
